Register	What it talks to
"	default Vim register
*	X11 primary selection
+	system clipboard
On macOS, both * and + usually map to the same system clipboard.
On Linux, they are different.


Two sets of shortcut to remember: 
"+yy (copy line to clipboard) and "+yy (copy line to selection); 
"+p (paste from clipboard) and 
"*p (paste from selection). 
" is to select register which is vim's own internal register by default 
(the way yy and p would work without referencing any type of register).


Add this to .vimrc:
set clipboard=unnamedplus
or
# mac
set clipboard=unnamed

"+y   copy to system clipboard
"+p   paste from system clipboard
"*y   copy to primary selection
"*p   paste from primary selection

